     <h1 class="background_aqua">
      This PETITION is now CLOSED
      <br />
      <br />
      It was presented to Council during the 708th Council Meeting
      <br />
      on 17th November 2015
      <br />
      <br />
      We achieved approximately 8,888 signatures
     </h1>
     <p>
     </p>
     <h3 class="text-left">
      Preamble:
      <br />
      <br />
      The
      <a target="new" href="http://www.goldcoast.qld.gov.au/thegoldcoast/oceanway-network-156.html">
       Gold Coast Oceanway
      </a>
      is a 36 kilometre network of pedestrian and cycling pathways along the foreshores from the Point Danger Lighthouse on the NSW border to the Gold Coast Seaway.  A world-class attraction, it has won numerous awards as a safe off-road route, widely utilised by the community and tourists alike.  The 1.7km Tugun to Bilinga section as a beachside Oceanway has been cancelled and will instead be built along busy Golden Four Drive.
      <br />
      <br />
      The Gold Coast City Council previously investigated and sought funding for the 1.7km Tugun to Bilinga section of the beachside Oceanway, receiving a grant of $2.3 Million from the SE Qld Cycle Network Program 2011-12 Capital Grants Projects. Council also allocated funding through its budget and prepared a detailed
      <a target="new" href="Images/report/t2b-planning-report.pdf">
       Planning Report
      </a>
      in October 2011 for this to be constructed.
      <br />
      <br />
      Local businesses, residents, ratepayers, international and Australian tourists and community groups including the Friends of Currumbin have all expressed support for the construction of the Tugun to Bilinga beachside section of the Oceanway.  However, on 22 June 2012, Gold Coast City Councillors voted not to proceed with the delivery of the Tugun to Bilinga Oceanway works as described in the Council commissioned
      <a target="new" href="Images/report/tugun-bilinga-consultation-report.pdf">
       Consultation Report
      </a>
      of May 2012 due to a flawed and biased survey that concluded there wasn’t community support for this Project.
     </h3>
     <br />
    </div>
    <div class="span12">
     <h1 class="text_drawing">
      <strong>
       We, respectfully petition the Gold Coast City Council to:
       <br />
       <br />
       1.  Reconsider Council's decision to reject the beachside Tugun to 	Bilinga section of the Oceanway,
       <br />
       2.  Accept Engineering Services completed Tugun to Bilinga Planning Report of 2011,
       <br />
       3.  Re-commit funds for construction to be completed by 2018.
      </strong>
      <br />
     </h1>
     <br />
